### Welcome to Bookis.me
It's a pretty stupid website

### Riker Ipsum
Mr. Worf, you sound like a man who's asking his friend if he can start dating his sister. Maybe if we felt any human loss as keenly as we feel one of those close to us, human history would be far less bloody. About four years. I got tired of hearing how young I looked. I am your worst nightmare!

### Sagan Ipsum
Science two ghostly white figures in coveralls and helmets are soflty dancing from which we spring across the centuries gathered by gravity Drake Equation hearts of the stars consciousness, muse about as a patch of light intelligent beings. Billions upon billions, dream of the mind's eye venture? Cosmos not a sunrise but a galaxyrise science the only home we've ever known trillion the sky calls to us Vangelis rogue hydrogen atoms Jean-François Champollion Cambrian explosion rogue realm of the galaxies Orion's sword citizens of distant epochs! Light years across the centuries Orion's sword.
Dream of the mind's eye! Consciousness, brain is the seed of intelligence corpus callosum cosmic ocean brain is the seed of intelligence trillion, galaxies realm of the galaxies circumnavigated Jean-François Champollion are creatures of the cosmos something incredible is waiting to be known rogue Orion's sword Tunguska event emerged into consciousness, take root and flourish muse about something incredible is waiting to be known hydrogen atoms. Ship of the imagination rogue brain is the seed of intelligence? Corpus callosum laws of physics, Sea of Tranquility gathered by gravity, Drake Equation consciousness, tesseract.
